   APT




    apt-transport-sftp
    APT transport via the SSH/SFTP protocol


Description

This APT transport allows the use of repositories accessed via the SSH File Transfer Protocol (SFTP).
It is available by default since apt 3.0 and was available before that in the package apt-transport-ssh.
Note that a transport is never called directly by a user but used by APT tools based on user configuration.


Client authentication

Besides supporting password-based authentication (see &apt-authconf;) SFTP also supports
authentication based on a private key via Acquire::sftp::PrivateKey and
an optional Acquire::sftp::PassPhrase.
The private key should be an RSA key, as generated via ssh-keygen -m PEM -t rsa -P "" -f id_rsa_PEM.
This should be set to the base-64 encoded part of the private key file;
the part between the -----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY----- and the corresponding footer.
The header and footer are generated using Acquire::sftp::PrivateKeyFromat, which defaults to RSA.



Examples

Acquire::sftp {
	PrivateKey "b4BjbnNz1CsrZ....
	PrivateKeyFromat "RSA";
	PassPhrase "secret";
};




